vely the electromagnetic fields,\nincluding the acceleration fields, even when they are at large distances from\nthe time-retarded position of the charge, they continue to be all around the\n`present' position of the charge which itself is moving toward infinity due to\nthe uniform acceleration.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Oct 2020 01:58:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 Jul 2021 15:31:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-04"}
